Toyota South Africa says deliveries of locally produced Hilux, Fortuner, and Corolla Cross vehicles continue to be delayed. (eNCA/Screenshot) JOHANNESBURG - Toyota South Africa says deliveries of locally produced Hilux, Fortuner, and Corolla Cross vehicles continue to be delayed. In an update on Friday it said its flood-hit Durban plant remains closed. However, the company says a meticulous phased plan to return the plant to working condition is underway. READ:Â KZN Floods | WATCH | Toyota plant puts brakes on production The good news is that the delivery of imported models is back at a usual pace. The company's plant in Prospecton, south of Durban suffered extensive damage in the floods. Thousands of vehicles have reportedly been written off.